summary: Captain Marvel is such an amwesome film. Watching this movie filled my heart with so much joy I can’t even begin to put it...
body:
Captain Marvel is such an amwesome film. Watching this movie filled my heart with so much joy I can’t even begin to put it coherently, but I’ll try.

There is just so much to love about it! Veers being just so cheeky. Her first interactions on earth involved Blockbuster and Radio Shack?! Her first encounter with Agent Fury and the rookie Phil Coulson was awesome! Maria Rambeau was so cool and I hope we see her again! Freaking Annette Benning!!! That Stan Lee tribute? And the 90s Stan Lee reference it made?! This 90’s kid was having the time of his life watching this movie

Spoilers Bellow:

.

.

.

.

.

.

.

Seriously just fly past this if you haven’t seen the movie yet

.

.

.

.

.

.

.

.

That moment when Carol realizes that the Kree have been inhibiting her power and she destroys the inhibitor was so freaking awesome!!! “I’ve been fighting with one hand tied behind my back” just made me like “oh fuck yes!” I cannot wait to see what she does in Avengers: Endgame. Also when she just like blasts Yon-Rogg into that rock formation instead of fighting him hand to hand! Lolol!!That gave me the same feeling I get when Indiana Jones just shrugs and shoots the sword guy in Raiders of the Lost Ark, but is even more satisfying because Yon-Rogg isn’t just a random henchman

as much as i love captain marvel, i do not want to see her taking out thanos or her being the main lead in taking out thanos.
it...
body:
as much as i love captain marvel, i do not want to see her taking out thanos or her being the main lead in taking out thanos.

it annoys me so much that people being like “she’s gonna end it” like no pls no. i know she’s powerful, but the og6 deserves to be the ones doing it specially Thor and tony. They all have a history with thanos, they all have suffered from thanos. I want all the new avengers to be important and be in action but satisfaction will only be when og6 will end it all.
